description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Infection Prevention &amp; Control Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base&lt;/strong&gt;: Wesleyan Building, Colmore Circus, Birmingham B4 6AR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Band&lt;/strong&gt;: 8a – 2 Positions (Full time &amp; Part time)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary&lt;/strong&gt;: £45,573-£51,668 per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Pattern&lt;/strong&gt;: Full time 37.5 hours per week and Part time 30 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type&lt;/strong&gt;: Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, dynamic and innovative individual to join our Infection Prevention and Control (IPC) team. We are looking for an experienced IPC Practitioner, with excellent interpersonal skills. You will need to be self-motivated, able to work independently, have a passion for IPC and the ability to influence and empower colleagues to deliver high standards of infection prevention and control practices. The successful candidate will work collaboratively with key stakeholders across the local and wider health economy, providing specialist knowledge and advice to BSOL CCG commissioning managers and system partners on all matters pertaining to Infection Prevention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Birmingham and Solihull Clinical Commissioning Group is the largest clinically-led commissioning organisation in England. We look after a population of around 1.3 million people. We are responsible for planning and commissioning health services for people living in Birmingham and Solihull and work as part of a large, complex system of health and social care which includes local authorities, providers, the independent sector and GP practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity and an exciting time to be a part of an experienced and committed service in a forward-thinking organisation and system. If you are hardworking, innovative and committed to making a difference, then we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CCG values diversity and welcomes Black and Minority Ethnic applicants to this role, where we are currently under-represented.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion/enquiries please contact Elizabeth Blackham, Strategic Lead for IPC via 07741168149 / elizabeth.blackham@nhs.net or Claire Underwood, Deputy Chief Nurse via 07881234918 / claire.underwood5@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: Friday 10th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
